England will play Italy in the Euro 2020 final on Sunday, July 11 at the Wembley Stadium. England had defeated Denmark 2-1 in the Euro 2020 semi-final some few days ago, while Italy eliminated Spain on penalties. Both teams have faced each other 27 times in the past. England have won 8 matches, while Italy have won 11 matches and the remaining 8 matches ended in a draw. The last time both sides came face-to-face was in a friendly in March 27, 2018. The friendly game ended in a 1-1 draw at Wembley, with Jamie Vardy and Lorenzo Insigne scoring for their respective teams. The match kicks off at 8 pm, Nigerian time. The match will be aired on DStv channel 204 and GOtv channel 32.